definitions.definition: Directly overhead ; vertically on top of.
Higher in the same page; earlier in the order as far as writing products go.
Into or from heaven; in the sky.
examples: He’s in a better place now, floating free as the clouds above .

definitions.definition: In a higher place; upstairs; farther upstream.
Higher in rank, power, or position.
examples: He appealed to the court above .
It was a cold day at only 5 above .
definitions.dating_raw: first attested in the mid 20 century.

definitions.definition: On the upper half or the dorsal surface of an animal.
examples: The sparrow I saw was rufous above and off-white below.

main_definition: Directly overhead ; vertically on top of. [first attested before 1150.]
secondary_definitions: Higher in the same page; earlier in the order as far as writing products go. [first attested before 1150.]
Into or from heaven; in the sky. [first attested around 1150–1350]
In a higher place; upstairs; farther upstream. [first attested around 1150–1350]
Higher in rank, power, or position. [first attested around 1150–1350]
Above zero; above freezing. [first attested in the mid 20 century.]
( biology ) On the upper half or the dorsal surface of an animal.
